<br>
There are different lives for a warrior. One pre-51, one 51-59 and one for the 60 crowd. My comments were directed at the 60 crowd mainly since that´s where most people spend the majority of their time and thus also what Verant mainly balances the game around (sorry, but that´s just the way it is).<br>
<br>
Pre-50 I can agree a warrior is less useful than a Pal/SK, due to many factors. Between 51 and 59 it evens out as warrior get nice discs, better gear and more.<br>
<br>
At 60 and above (i.e. plenty AA skills) I think the warriors fill their role pretty well. As Raiya said skills are in the hands of the player as well as in the class/race.<br>
<br>
I don´t see why people argue how hard it is for a warrior to taunt off a chanter/shammie when they slow. You do realize the enormous benefit a slowed mob means, right ? Besides there are ways around it (slow later, mem blur, root etc).<br>
<br>
Personally I´d take a warrior over a Pal/SK most any day, but there are still situations (FD puller needed, fighting undeads) where the hybrids shine through. As a pure meatshield, they can´t beat the warrior though. It´s up to the group to adapt their playstyle though.<br>
<br>
Although I think they could up the skill &quot;taunt&quot; a tad to make it more viable, I fear it would &quot;dumbify&quot; EQ even more, and I see enough people playing with their heads up their ass as is ;P<br>
<br>
Just my $0.02<br>
<br>
-Fubbik-<br>
